# Playwright quick gates (mandatory before run)

Before proposing or running **any** Playwright command (`npx playwright test`, export/render smoke, trace viewer), run the stack health gates from repo root. **Do not** launch Playwright when gates fail — auth/timeouts are usually upstream (502 API, 500 web, missing seed, stale `.auth` cookies).

## Layout detection

| Repo layout | Suite README (read first) |
|---|---|
| `apps/web/e2e/**` | `apps/web/e2e/README.md` |
| `e2e/playwright/**` | `e2e/playwright/README-maintainers.md` (+ captcha todos if present) |

Platform test map (when present): `docs/TESTING.md` § L5.

## Procedure

Follow the **`playwright-runner-docs-gate`** skill — it contains the copy-paste gate block, Playwright Docker one-shot template, trace viewer, and MRP/CRP export troubleshooting pointers.

## Hard stops

- `GET /api/health` not `{"ok":true}` → fix api container before Playwright.
- Login page not HTTP 200 → fix web container before Playwright.
- `seed:e2e` (or project equivalent) not run when specs use seeded personas.
- After stack recovery: delete stale `apps/web/e2e/.auth/*.json` (or project equivalent) if sessions fail despite healthy health checks.
